55/*
56 Various border types, image boundaries are denoted with '|'
57
58 * BORDER_REPLICATE: aaaaaa|abcdefgh|hhhhhhh
59 * BORDER_REFLECT: fedcba|abcdefgh|hgfedcb
60 * BORDER_REFLECT_101: gfedcb|abcdefgh|gfedcba
61 * BORDER_WRAP: cdefgh|abcdefgh|abcdefg
62 * BORDER_CONSTANT: iiiiii|abcdefgh|iiiiiii with some specified 'i'
63 */
64int cv::borderInterpolate( int p, int len, int borderType )
65{
66 if( (unsigned)p < (unsigned)len )
67 ;
68 else if( borderType == BORDER_REPLICATE )
69 p = p < 0 ? 0 : len - 1;
70 else if( borderType == BORDER_REFLECT || borderType == BORDER_REFLECT_101 )
71 {
72 int delta = borderType == BORDER_REFLECT_101;
73 if( len == 1 )
74 return 0;
75 do
76 {
77 if( p < 0 )
78 p = -p - 1 + delta;
79 else
80 p = len - 1 - (p - len) - delta;
81 }
82 while( (unsigned)p >= (unsigned)len );
83 }
84 else if( borderType == BORDER_WRAP )
85 {
86 if( p < 0 )
87 p -= ((p-len+1)/len)*len;
88 if( p >= len )
89 p %= len;
90 }
91 else if( borderType == BORDER_CONSTANT )
92 p = -1;
93 else
94 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown/unsupported border type" );
95 return p;
96}

113FilterEngine::FilterEngine()
114{
115 srcType = dstType = bufType = -1;
116 rowBorderType = columnBorderType = BORDER_REPLICATE;
117 bufStep = startY = startY0 = endY = rowCount = dstY = 0;
118 maxWidth = 0;
119
120 wholeSize = Size(-1,-1);
121}

140void FilterEngine::init( const Ptr<BaseFilter>& _filter2D,
141 const Ptr<BaseRowFilter>& _rowFilter,
142 const Ptr<BaseColumnFilter>& _columnFilter,
143 int _srcType, int _dstType, int _bufType,
144 int _rowBorderType, int _columnBorderType,
145 const Scalar& _borderValue )
146{
147 _srcType = CV_MAT_TYPE(_srcType);
148 _bufType = CV_MAT_TYPE(_bufType);
149 _dstType = CV_MAT_TYPE(_dstType);
150
151 srcType = _srcType;
152 int srcElemSize = (int)getElemSize(srcType);
153 dstType = _dstType;
154 bufType = _bufType;
155
156 filter2D = _filter2D;
157 rowFilter = _rowFilter;
158 columnFilter = _columnFilter;
159
160 if( _columnBorderType < 0 )
161 _columnBorderType = _rowBorderType;
162
163 rowBorderType = _rowBorderType;
164 columnBorderType = _columnBorderType;
165
166 CV_Assert( columnBorderType != BORDER_WRAP );
167
168 if( isSeparable() )
169 {
170 CV_Assert( !rowFilter.empty() && !columnFilter.empty() );
171 ksize = Size(rowFilter->ksize, columnFilter->ksize);
172 anchor = Point(rowFilter->anchor, columnFilter->anchor);
173 }
174 else
175 {
176 CV_Assert( bufType == srcType );
177 ksize = filter2D->ksize;
178 anchor = filter2D->anchor;
179 }
180
181 CV_Assert( 0 <= anchor.x && anchor.x < ksize.width &&
182 0 <= anchor.y && anchor.y < ksize.height );
183
184 borderElemSize = srcElemSize/(CV_MAT_DEPTH(srcType) >= CV_32S ? sizeof(int) : 1);
185 int borderLength = std::max(ksize.width - 1, 1);
186 borderTab.resize(borderLength*borderElemSize);
187
188 maxWidth = bufStep = 0;
189 constBorderRow.clear();
190
191 if( rowBorderType == BORDER_CONSTANT || columnBorderType == BORDER_CONSTANT )
192 {
193 constBorderValue.resize(srcElemSize*borderLength);
194 int srcType1 = CV_MAKETYPE(CV_MAT_DEPTH(srcType), MIN(CV_MAT_CN(srcType), 4));
195 scalarToRawData(_borderValue, &constBorderValue[0], srcType1,
196 borderLength*CV_MAT_CN(srcType));
197 }
198
199 wholeSize = Size(-1,-1);
200}
201
202static const int VEC_ALIGN = CV_MALLOC_ALIGN;
203
204int FilterEngine::start(Size _wholeSize, Rect _roi, int _maxBufRows)
205{
206 int i, j;
207
208 wholeSize = _wholeSize;
209 roi = _roi;
210 CV_Assert( roi.x >= 0 && roi.y >= 0 && roi.width >= 0 && roi.height >= 0 &&
211 roi.x + roi.width <= wholeSize.width &&
212 roi.y + roi.height <= wholeSize.height );
213
214 int esz = (int)getElemSize(srcType);
215 int bufElemSize = (int)getElemSize(bufType);
216 const uchar* constVal = !constBorderValue.empty() ? &constBorderValue[0] : 0;
217
218 if( _maxBufRows < 0 )
219 _maxBufRows = ksize.height + 3;
220 _maxBufRows = std::max(_maxBufRows, std::max(anchor.y, ksize.height-anchor.y-1)*2+1);
221
222 if( maxWidth < roi.width || _maxBufRows != (int)rows.size() )
223 {
224 rows.resize(_maxBufRows);
225 maxWidth = std::max(maxWidth, roi.width);
226 int cn = CV_MAT_CN(srcType);
227 srcRow.resize(esz*(maxWidth + ksize.width - 1));
228 if( columnBorderType == BORDER_CONSTANT )
229 {
230 constBorderRow.resize(getElemSize(bufType)*(maxWidth + ksize.width - 1 + VEC_ALIGN));
231 uchar *dst = alignPtr(&constBorderRow[0], VEC_ALIGN), *tdst;
232 int n = (int)constBorderValue.size(), N;
233 N = (maxWidth + ksize.width - 1)*esz;
234 tdst = isSeparable() ? &srcRow[0] : dst;
235
236 for( i = 0; i < N; i += n )
237 {
238 n = std::min( n, N - i );
239 for(j = 0; j < n; j++)
240 tdst[i+j] = constVal[j];
241 }
242
243 if( isSeparable() )
244 (*rowFilter)(&srcRow[0], dst, maxWidth, cn);
245 }
246
247 int maxBufStep = bufElemSize*(int)alignSize(maxWidth +
248 (!isSeparable() ? ksize.width - 1 : 0),VEC_ALIGN);
249 ringBuf.resize(maxBufStep*rows.size()+VEC_ALIGN);
250 }
251
252 // adjust bufstep so that the used part of the ring buffer stays compact in memory
253 bufStep = bufElemSize*(int)alignSize(roi.width + (!isSeparable() ? ksize.width - 1 : 0),16);
254
255 dx1 = std::max(anchor.x - roi.x, 0);
256 dx2 = std::max(ksize.width - anchor.x - 1 + roi.x + roi.width - wholeSize.width, 0);
257
258 // recompute border tables
259 if( dx1 > 0 || dx2 > 0 )
260 {
261 if( rowBorderType == BORDER_CONSTANT )
262 {
263 int nr = isSeparable() ? 1 : (int)rows.size();
264 for( i = 0; i < nr; i++ )
265 {
266 uchar* dst = isSeparable() ? &srcRow[0] : alignPtr(&ringBuf[0],VEC_ALIGN) + bufStep*i;
267 memcpy( dst, constVal, dx1*esz );
268 memcpy( dst + (roi.width + ksize.width - 1 - dx2)*esz, constVal, dx2*esz );
269 }
270 }
271 else
272 {
273 int xofs1 = std::min(roi.x, anchor.x) - roi.x;
274
275 int btab_esz = borderElemSize, wholeWidth = wholeSize.width;
276 int* btab = (int*)&borderTab[0];
277
278 for( i = 0; i < dx1; i++ )
279 {
280 int p0 = (borderInterpolate(i-dx1, wholeWidth, rowBorderType) + xofs1)*btab_esz;
281 for( j = 0; j < btab_esz; j++ )
282 btab[i*btab_esz + j] = p0 + j;
283 }
284
285 for( i = 0; i < dx2; i++ )
286 {
287 int p0 = (borderInterpolate(wholeWidth + i, wholeWidth, rowBorderType) + xofs1)*btab_esz;
288 for( j = 0; j < btab_esz; j++ )
289 btab[(i + dx1)*btab_esz + j] = p0 + j;
290 }
291 }
292 }
293
294 rowCount = dstY = 0;
295 startY = startY0 = std::max(roi.y - anchor.y, 0);
296 endY = std::min(roi.y + roi.height + ksize.height - anchor.y - 1, wholeSize.height);
297 if( !columnFilter.empty() )
298 columnFilter->reset();
299 if( !filter2D.empty() )
300 filter2D->reset();
301
302 return startY;
303}

305
306int FilterEngine::start(const Mat& src, const Rect& _srcRoi,
307 bool isolated, int maxBufRows)
308{
309 Rect srcRoi = _srcRoi;
310
311 if( srcRoi == Rect(0,0,-1,-1) )
312 srcRoi = Rect(0,0,src.cols,src.rows);
313
314 CV_Assert( srcRoi.x >= 0 && srcRoi.y >= 0 &&
315 srcRoi.width >= 0 && srcRoi.height >= 0 &&
316 srcRoi.x + srcRoi.width <= src.cols &&
317 srcRoi.y + srcRoi.height <= src.rows );
318
319 Point ofs;
320 Size wsz(src.cols, src.rows);
321 if( !isolated )
322 src.locateROI( wsz, ofs );
323 start( wsz, srcRoi + ofs, maxBufRows );
324
325 return startY - ofs.y;
326}
327
328
329int FilterEngine::remainingInputRows() const
330{
331 return endY - startY - rowCount;
332}
333
334int FilterEngine::remainingOutputRows() const
335{
336 return roi.height - dstY;
337}
338
339int FilterEngine::proceed( const uchar* src, int srcstep, int count,
340 uchar* dst, int dststep )
341{
342 CV_Assert( wholeSize.width > 0 && wholeSize.height > 0 );
343
344 const int *btab = &borderTab[0];
345 int esz = (int)getElemSize(srcType), btab_esz = borderElemSize;
346 uchar** brows = &rows[0];
347 int bufRows = (int)rows.size();
348 int cn = CV_MAT_CN(bufType);
349 int width = roi.width, kwidth = ksize.width;
350 int kheight = ksize.height, ay = anchor.y;
351 int _dx1 = dx1, _dx2 = dx2;
352 int width1 = roi.width + kwidth - 1;
353 int xofs1 = std::min(roi.x, anchor.x);
354 bool isSep = isSeparable();
355 bool makeBorder = (_dx1 > 0 || _dx2 > 0) && rowBorderType != BORDER_CONSTANT;
356 int dy = 0, i = 0;
357
358 src -= xofs1*esz;
359 count = std::min(count, remainingInputRows());
360
361 CV_Assert( src && dst && count > 0 );
362
363 for(;; dst += dststep*i, dy += i)
364 {
365 int dcount = bufRows - ay - startY - rowCount + roi.y;
366 dcount = dcount > 0 ? dcount : bufRows - kheight + 1;
367 dcount = std::min(dcount, count);
368 count -= dcount;
369 for( ; dcount-- > 0; src += srcstep )
370 {
371 int bi = (startY - startY0 + rowCount) % bufRows;
372 uchar* brow = alignPtr(&ringBuf[0], VEC_ALIGN) + bi*bufStep;
373 uchar* row = isSep ? &srcRow[0] : brow;
374
375 if( ++rowCount > bufRows )
376 {
377 --rowCount;
378 ++startY;
379 }
380
381 memcpy( row + _dx1*esz, src, (width1 - _dx2 - _dx1)*esz );
382
383 if( makeBorder )
384 {
385 if( btab_esz*(int)sizeof(int) == esz )
386 {
387 const int* isrc = (const int*)src;
388 int* irow = (int*)row;
389
390 for( i = 0; i < _dx1*btab_esz; i++ )
391 irow[i] = isrc[btab[i]];
392 for( i = 0; i < _dx2*btab_esz; i++ )
393 irow[i + (width1 - _dx2)*btab_esz] = isrc[btab[i+_dx1*btab_esz]];
394 }
395 else
396 {
397 for( i = 0; i < _dx1*esz; i++ )
398 row[i] = src[btab[i]];
399 for( i = 0; i < _dx2*esz; i++ )
400 row[i + (width1 - _dx2)*esz] = src[btab[i+_dx1*esz]];
401 }
402 }
403
404 if( isSep )
405 (*rowFilter)(row, brow, width, CV_MAT_CN(srcType));
406 }
407
408 int max_i = std::min(bufRows, roi.height - (dstY + dy) + (kheight - 1));
409 for( i = 0; i < max_i; i++ )
410 {
411 int srcY = borderInterpolate(dstY + dy + i + roi.y - ay,
412 wholeSize.height, columnBorderType);
413 if( srcY < 0 ) // can happen only with constant border type
414 brows[i] = alignPtr(&constBorderRow[0], VEC_ALIGN);
415 else
416 {
417 CV_Assert( srcY >= startY );
418 if( srcY >= startY + rowCount )
419 break;
420 int bi = (srcY - startY0) % bufRows;
421 brows[i] = alignPtr(&ringBuf[0], VEC_ALIGN) + bi*bufStep;
422 }
423 }
424 if( i < kheight )
425 break;
426 i -= kheight - 1;
427 if( isSeparable() )
428 (*columnFilter)((const uchar**)brows, dst, dststep, i, roi.width*cn);
429 else
430 (*filter2D)((const uchar**)brows, dst, dststep, i, roi.width, cn);
431 }
432
433 dstY += dy;
434 CV_Assert( dstY <= roi.height );
435 return dy;
436}
437
438
439void FilterEngine::apply(const Mat& src, Mat& dst,
440 const Rect& _srcRoi, Point dstOfs, bool isolated)
441{
442 CV_Assert( src.type() == srcType && dst.type() == dstType );
443
444 Rect srcRoi = _srcRoi;
445 if( srcRoi == Rect(0,0,-1,-1) )
446 srcRoi = Rect(0,0,src.cols,src.rows);
447
448 if( srcRoi.area() == 0 )
449 return;
450
451 CV_Assert( dstOfs.x >= 0 && dstOfs.y >= 0 &&
452 dstOfs.x + srcRoi.width <= dst.cols &&
453 dstOfs.y + srcRoi.height <= dst.rows );
454
455 int y = start(src, srcRoi, isolated);
456 proceed( src.data + y*src.step
457 + srcRoi.x*src.elemSize(),
458 (int)src.step, endY - startY,
459 dst.data + dstOfs.y*dst.step +
460 dstOfs.x*dst.elemSize(), (int)dst.step );
461}

465/****************************************************************************************\
466* Separable linear filter *
467\****************************************************************************************/
468
469int cv::getKernelType(InputArray filter_kernel, Point anchor)
470{
471 Mat _kernel = filter_kernel.getMat();
472 CV_Assert( _kernel.channels() == 1 );
473 int i, sz = _kernel.rows*_kernel.cols;
474
475 Mat kernel;
476 _kernel.convertTo(kernel, CV_64F);
477
478 const double* coeffs = (double*)kernel.data;
479 double sum = 0;
480 int type = KERNEL_SMOOTH + KERNEL_INTEGER;
481 if( (_kernel.rows == 1 || _kernel.cols == 1) &&
482 anchor.x*2 + 1 == _kernel.cols &&
483 anchor.y*2 + 1 == _kernel.rows )
484 type |= (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL + KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL);
485
486 for( i = 0; i < sz; i++ )
487 {
488 double a = coeffs[i], b = coeffs[sz - i - 1];
489 if( a != b )
490 type &= ~KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL;
491 if( a != -b )
492 type &= ~KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL;
493 if( a < 0 )
494 type &= ~KERNEL_SMOOTH;
495 if( a != saturate_cast<int>(a) )
496 type &= ~KERNEL_INTEGER;
497 sum += a;
498 }
499
500 if( fabs(sum - 1) > FLT_EPSILON*(fabs(sum) + 1) )
501 type &= ~KERNEL_SMOOTH;
502 return type;
503}

547///////////////////////////////////// 8u-16s & 8u-8u //////////////////////////////////
548
549struct RowVec_8u32s
550{
551 RowVec_8u32s() { smallValues = false; }
552 RowVec_8u32s( const Mat& _kernel )
553 {
554 kernel = _kernel;
555 smallValues = true;
556 int k, ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
557 for( k = 0; k < ksize; k++ )
558 {
559 int v = ((const int*)kernel.data)[k];
560 if( v < SHRT_MIN || v > SHRT_MAX )
561 {
562 smallValues = false;
563 break;
564 }
565 }
566 }
567
568 int operator()(const uchar* _src, uchar* _dst, int width, int cn) const
569 {
570 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2) )
571 return 0;
572
573 int i = 0, k, _ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
574 int* dst = (int*)_dst;
575 const int* _kx = (const int*)kernel.data;
576 width *= cn;
577
578 if( smallValues )
579 {
580 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
581 {
582 const uchar* src = _src + i;
583 __m128i f, z = _mm_setzero_si128(), s0 = z, s1 = z, s2 = z, s3 = z;
584 __m128i x0, x1, x2, x3;
585
586 for( k = 0; k < _ksize; k++, src += cn )
587 {
588 f = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(_kx[k]);
589 f = _mm_shuffle_epi32(f, 0);
590 f = _mm_packs_epi32(f, f);
591
592 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)src);
593 x2 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z);
594 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
595 x1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, f);
596 x3 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x2, f);
597 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, f);
598 x2 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x2, f);
599
600 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x1));
601 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(s1, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x1));
602 s2 = _mm_add_epi32(s2, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x2, x3));
603 s3 = _mm_add_epi32(s3, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x2, x3));
604 }
605
606 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), s0);
607 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), s1);
608 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), s2);
609 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), s3);
610 }
611
612 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
613 {
614 const uchar* src = _src + i;
615 __m128i f, z = _mm_setzero_si128(), s0 = z, x0, x1;
616
617 for( k = 0; k < _ksize; k++, src += cn )
618 {
619 f = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(_kx[k]);
620 f = _mm_shuffle_epi32(f, 0);
621 f = _mm_packs_epi32(f, f);
622
623 x0 = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(*(const int*)src);
624 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
625 x1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, f);
626 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, f);
627 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x1));
628 }
629 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), s0);
630 }
631 }
632 return i;
633 }
634
635 Mat kernel;
636 bool smallValues;
637};
638
639
640struct SymmRowSmallVec_8u32s
641{
642 SymmRowSmallVec_8u32s() { smallValues = false; }
643 SymmRowSmallVec_8u32s( const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType )
644 {
645 kernel = _kernel;
646 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
647 smallValues = true;
648 int k, ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
649 for( k = 0; k < ksize; k++ )
650 {
651 int v = ((const int*)kernel.data)[k];
652 if( v < SHRT_MIN || v > SHRT_MAX )
653 {
654 smallValues = false;
655 break;
656 }
657 }
658 }
659
660 int operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* _dst, int width, int cn) const
661 {
662 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2) )
663 return 0;
664
665 int i = 0, j, k, _ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
666 int* dst = (int*)_dst;
667 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
668 const int* kx = (const int*)kernel.data + _ksize/2;
669 if( !smallValues )
670 return 0;
671
672 src += (_ksize/2)*cn;
673 width *= cn;
674
675 __m128i z = _mm_setzero_si128();
676 if( symmetrical )
677 {
678 if( _ksize == 1 )
679 return 0;
680 if( _ksize == 3 )
681 {
682 if( kx[0] == 2 && kx[1] == 1 )
683 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
684 {
685 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
686 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
687 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)src);
688 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
689 y0 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z);
690 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
691 y1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z);
692 x1 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z);
693 y2 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z);
694 x2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z);
695 x0 = _mm_add_epi16(x0, _mm_add_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(x1, x1), x2));
696 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(y0, _mm_add_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(y1, y1), y2));
697 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, z));
698 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, z));
699 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, z));
700 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, z));
701 }
702 else if( kx[0] == -2 && kx[1] == 1 )
703 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
704 {
705 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
706 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
707 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)src);
708 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
709 y0 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z);
710 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
711 y1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z);
712 x1 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z);
713 y2 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z);
714 x2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z);
715 x0 = _mm_add_epi16(x0, _mm_sub_epi16(x2, _mm_add_epi16(x1, x1)));
716 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(y0, _mm_sub_epi16(y2, _mm_add_epi16(y1, y1)));
717 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x0),16));
718 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x0),16));
719 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y0),16));
720 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y0),16));
721 }
722 else
723 {
724 __m128i k0 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[0]), 0),
725 k1 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[1]), 0);
726 k0 = _mm_packs_epi32(k0, k0);
727 k1 = _mm_packs_epi32(k1, k1);
728
729 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
730 {
731 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, t0, t1, z0, z1, z2, z3;
732 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
733 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)src);
734 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
735 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z));
736 x0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z));
737 y1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z);
738 x1 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z);
739
740 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x1, k0);
741 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x1, k0);
742 x2 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, k1);
743 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, k1);
744 z0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1);
745 z1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1);
746 z0 = _mm_add_epi32(z0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x2));
747 z1 = _mm_add_epi32(z1, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x2));
748
749 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y1, k0);
750 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y1, k0);
751 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k1);
752 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k1);
753 z2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1);
754 z3 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1);
755 z2 = _mm_add_epi32(z2, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1));
756 z3 = _mm_add_epi32(z3, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1));
757 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), z0);
758 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), z1);
759 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), z2);
760 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), z3);
761 }
762 }
763 }
764 else if( _ksize == 5 )
765 {
766 if( kx[0] == -2 && kx[1] == 0 && kx[2] == 1 )
767 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
768 {
769 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
770 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn*2));
771 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)src);
772 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn*2));
773 y0 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z);
774 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
775 y1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z);
776 x1 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z);
777 y2 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z);
778 x2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z);
779 x0 = _mm_add_epi16(x0, _mm_sub_epi16(x2, _mm_add_epi16(x1, x1)));
780 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(y0, _mm_sub_epi16(y2, _mm_add_epi16(y1, y1)));
781 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x0),16));
782 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x0),16));
783 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y0),16));
784 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y0),16));
785 }
786 else
787 {
788 __m128i k0 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[0]), 0),
789 k1 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[1]), 0),
790 k2 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[2]), 0);
791 k0 = _mm_packs_epi32(k0, k0);
792 k1 = _mm_packs_epi32(k1, k1);
793 k2 = _mm_packs_epi32(k2, k2);
794
795 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
796 {
797 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, t0, t1, z0, z1, z2, z3;
798 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
799 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)src);
800 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
801 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z));
802 x0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z));
803 y1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z);
804 x1 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z);
805
806 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x1, k0);
807 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x1, k0);
808 x2 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, k1);
809 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, k1);
810 z0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1);
811 z1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1);
812 z0 = _mm_add_epi32(z0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x2));
813 z1 = _mm_add_epi32(z1, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x2));
814
815 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y1, k0);
816 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y1, k0);
817 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k1);
818 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k1);
819 z2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1);
820 z3 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1);
821 z2 = _mm_add_epi32(z2, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1));
822 z3 = _mm_add_epi32(z3, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1));
823
824 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn*2));
825 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn*2));
826 y1 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z));
827 y0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z));
828
829 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k2);
830 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k2);
831 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y1, k2);
832 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y1, k2);
833 z0 = _mm_add_epi32(z0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1));
834 z1 = _mm_add_epi32(z1, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1));
835 z2 = _mm_add_epi32(z2, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1));
836 z3 = _mm_add_epi32(z3, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1));
837
838 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), z0);
839 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), z1);
840 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), z2);
841 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), z3);
842 }
843 }
844 }
845 }
846 else
847 {
848 if( _ksize == 3 )
849 {
850 if( kx[0] == 0 && kx[1] == 1 )
851 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
852 {
853 __m128i x0, x1, y0;
854 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
855 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
856 y0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z));
857 x0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z));
858 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x0),16));
859 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x0),16));
860 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y0),16));
861 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y0),16));
862 }
863 else
864 {
865 __m128i k1 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[1]), 0);
866 k1 = _mm_packs_epi32(k1, k1);
867
868 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
869 {
870 __m128i x0, x1, y0, y1, z0, z1, z2, z3;
871 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
872 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
873 y0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z));
874 x0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z));
875
876 x1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, k1);
877 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, k1);
878 z0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x1);
879 z1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x1);
880
881 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k1);
882 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k1);
883 z2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1);
884 z3 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1);
885 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), z0);
886 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), z1);
887 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), z2);
888 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), z3);
889 }
890 }
891 }
892 else if( _ksize == 5 )
893 {
894 __m128i k0 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[0]), 0),
895 k1 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[1]), 0),
896 k2 = _mm_shuffle_epi32(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[2]), 0);
897 k0 = _mm_packs_epi32(k0, k0);
898 k1 = _mm_packs_epi32(k1, k1);
899 k2 = _mm_packs_epi32(k2, k2);
900
901 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16, src += 16 )
902 {
903 __m128i x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, t0, t1, z0, z1, z2, z3;
904 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn));
905 x2 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn));
906 y0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x2, z));
907 x0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x2, z));
908
909 x2 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, k1);
910 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, k1);
911 z0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x2);
912 z1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, x2);
913 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k1);
914 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k1);
915 z2 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1);
916 z3 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1);
917
918 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src + cn*2));
919 x1 = _mm_loadu_si128((__m128i*)(src - cn*2));
920 y1 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x1, z));
921 y0 = _mm_sub_epi16(_mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z), _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x1, z));
922
923 t1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y0, k2);
924 t0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y0, k2);
925 y0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(y1, k2);
926 y1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(y1, k2);
927 z0 = _mm_add_epi32(z0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(t0, t1));
928 z1 = _mm_add_epi32(z1, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(t0, t1));
929 z2 = _mm_add_epi32(z2, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(y0, y1));
930 z3 = _mm_add_epi32(z3, _mm_unpackhi_epi16(y0, y1));
931
932 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), z0);
933 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 4), z1);
934 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), z2);
935 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 12), z3);
936 }
937 }
938 }
939
940 src -= (_ksize/2)*cn;
941 kx -= _ksize/2;
942 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4, src += 4 )
943 {
944 __m128i f, s0 = z, x0, x1;
945
946 for( k = j = 0; k < _ksize; k++, j += cn )
947 {
948 f = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(kx[k]);
949 f = _mm_shuffle_epi32(f, 0);
950 f = _mm_packs_epi32(f, f);
951
952 x0 = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(*(const int*)(src + j));
953 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
954 x1 = _mm_mulhi_epi16(x0, f);
955 x0 = _mm_mullo_epi16(x0, f);
956 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, _mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, x1));
957 }
958 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), s0);
959 }
960
961 return i;
962 }
963
964 Mat kernel;
965 int symmetryType;
966 bool smallValues;
967};
968
969
970struct SymmColumnVec_32s8u
971{
972 SymmColumnVec_32s8u() { symmetryType=0; }
973 SymmColumnVec_32s8u(const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType, int _bits, double _delta)
974 {
975 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
976 _kernel.convertTo(kernel, CV_32F, 1./(1 << _bits), 0);
977 delta = (float)(_delta/(1 << _bits));
978 CV_Assert( (symmetryType & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL | KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) != 0 );
979 }
980
981 int operator()(const uchar** _src, uchar* dst, int width) const
982 {
983 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2) )
984 return 0;
985
986 int ksize2 = (kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1)/2;
987 const float* ky = (const float*)kernel.data + ksize2;
988 int i = 0, k;
989 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
990 const int** src = (const int**)_src;
991 const __m128i *S, *S2;
992 __m128 d4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
993
994 if( symmetrical )
995 {
996 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
997 {
998 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
999 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1000 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1001 __m128i x0, x1;
1002 S = (const __m128i*)(src[0] + i);
1003 s0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128(S));
1004 s1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128(S+1));
1005 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1006 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s1, f), d4);
1007 s2 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128(S+2));
1008 s3 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128(S+3));
1009 s2 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s2, f), d4);
1010 s3 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s3, f), d4);
1011
1012 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1013 {
1014 S = (const __m128i*)(src[k] + i);
1015 S2 = (const __m128i*)(src[-k] + i);
1016 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1017 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1018 x0 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S), _mm_load_si128(S2));
1019 x1 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+1), _mm_load_si128(S2+1));
1020 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1021 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1), f));
1022 x0 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+2), _mm_load_si128(S2+2));
1023 x1 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+3), _mm_load_si128(S2+3));
1024 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1025 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1), f));
1026 }
1027
1028 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1));
1029 x1 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s2), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s3));
1030 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x1);
1031 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), x0);
1032 }
1033
1034 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1035 {
1036 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
1037 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1038 __m128i x0;
1039 __m128 s0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128((const __m128i*)(src[0] + i)));
1040 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1041
1042 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1043 {
1044 S = (const __m128i*)(src[k] + i);
1045 S2 = (const __m128i*)(src[-k] + i);
1046 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1047 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1048 x0 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S), _mm_load_si128(S2));
1049 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1050 }
1051
1052 x0 = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1053 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(x0, x0);
1054 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x0);
1055 *(int*)(dst + i) = _mm_cvtsi128_si32(x0);
1056 }
1057 }
1058 else
1059 {
1060 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
1061 {
1062 __m128 f, s0 = d4, s1 = d4, s2 = d4, s3 = d4;
1063 __m128i x0, x1;
1064
1065 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1066 {
1067 S = (const __m128i*)(src[k] + i);
1068 S2 = (const __m128i*)(src[-k] + i);
1069 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1070 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1071 x0 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S), _mm_load_si128(S2));
1072 x1 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+1), _mm_load_si128(S2+1));
1073 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1074 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1), f));
1075 x0 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+2), _mm_load_si128(S2+2));
1076 x1 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S+3), _mm_load_si128(S2+3));
1077 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1078 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1), f));
1079 }
1080
1081 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1));
1082 x1 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s2), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s3));
1083 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x1);
1084 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), x0);
1085 }
1086
1087 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1088 {
1089 __m128 f, s0 = d4;
1090 __m128i x0;
1091
1092 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1093 {
1094 S = (const __m128i*)(src[k] + i);
1095 S2 = (const __m128i*)(src[-k] + i);
1096 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1097 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1098 x0 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128(S), _mm_load_si128(S2));
1099 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0), f));
1100 }
1101
1102 x0 = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1103 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(x0, x0);
1104 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x0);
1105 *(int*)(dst + i) = _mm_cvtsi128_si32(x0);
1106 }
1107 }
1108
1109 return i;
1110 }
1111
1112 int symmetryType;
1113 float delta;
1114 Mat kernel;
1115};

1118struct SymmColumnSmallVec_32s16s
1119{
1120 SymmColumnSmallVec_32s16s() { symmetryType=0; }
1121 SymmColumnSmallVec_32s16s(const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType, int _bits, double _delta)
1122 {
1123 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
1124 _kernel.convertTo(kernel, CV_32F, 1./(1 << _bits), 0);
1125 delta = (float)(_delta/(1 << _bits));
1126 CV_Assert( (symmetryType & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL | KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) != 0 );
1127 }
1128
1129 int operator()(const uchar** _src, uchar* _dst, int width) const
1130 {
1131 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2) )
1132 return 0;
1133
1134 int ksize2 = (kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1)/2;
1135 const float* ky = (const float*)kernel.data + ksize2;
1136 int i = 0;
1137 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
1138 const int** src = (const int**)_src;
1139 const int *S0 = src[-1], *S1 = src[0], *S2 = src[1];
1140 short* dst = (short*)_dst;
1141 __m128 df4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
1142 __m128i d4 = _mm_cvtps_epi32(df4);
1143
1144 if( symmetrical )
1145 {
1146 if( ky[0] == 2 && ky[1] == 1 )
1147 {
1148 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1149 {
1150 __m128i s0, s1, s2, s3, s4, s5;
1151 s0 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i));
1152 s1 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i + 4));
1153 s2 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i));
1154 s3 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i + 4));
1155 s4 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i));
1156 s5 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i + 4));
1157 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, _mm_add_epi32(s4, _mm_add_epi32(s2, s2)));
1158 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(s1, _mm_add_epi32(s5, _mm_add_epi32(s3, s3)));
1159 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, d4);
1160 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(s1, d4);
1161 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0, s1));
1162 }
1163 }
1164 else if( ky[0] == -2 && ky[1] == 1 )
1165 {
1166 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1167 {
1168 __m128i s0, s1, s2, s3, s4, s5;
1169 s0 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i));
1170 s1 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i + 4));
1171 s2 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i));
1172 s3 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i + 4));
1173 s4 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i));
1174 s5 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i + 4));
1175 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, _mm_sub_epi32(s4, _mm_add_epi32(s2, s2)));
1176 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(s1, _mm_sub_epi32(s5, _mm_add_epi32(s3, s3)));
1177 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(s0, d4);
1178 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(s1, d4);
1179 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0, s1));
1180 }
1181 }
1182 else
1183 {
1184 __m128 k0 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[0]), k1 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[1]);
1185 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1186 {
1187 __m128 s0, s1;
1188 s0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i)));
1189 s1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S1 + i + 4)));
1190 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, k0), df4);
1191 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s1, k0), df4);
1192 __m128i x0, x1;
1193 x0 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i)),
1194 _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i)));
1195 x1 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i + 4)),
1196 _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i + 4)));
1197 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0),k1));
1198 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1),k1));
1199 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1));
1200 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), x0);
1201 }
1202 }
1203 }
1204 else
1205 {
1206 if( fabs(ky[1]) == 1 && ky[1] == -ky[-1] )
1207 {
1208 if( ky[1] < 0 )
1209 std::swap(S0, S2);
1210 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1211 {
1212 __m128i s0, s1, s2, s3;
1213 s0 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i));
1214 s1 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i + 4));
1215 s2 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i));
1216 s3 = _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i + 4));
1217 s0 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_sub_epi32(s0, s2), d4);
1218 s1 = _mm_add_epi32(_mm_sub_epi32(s1, s3), d4);
1219 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0, s1));
1220 }
1221 }
1222 else
1223 {
1224 __m128 k1 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[1]);
1225 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1226 {
1227 __m128 s0 = df4, s1 = df4;
1228 __m128i x0, x1;
1229 x0 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i)),
1230 _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i)));
1231 x1 = _mm_sub_epi32(_mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S0 + i + 4)),
1232 _mm_load_si128((__m128i*)(S2 + i + 4)));
1233 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0),k1));
1234 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(_mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1),k1));
1235 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1));
1236 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), x0);
1237 }
1238 }
1239 }
1240
1241 return i;
1242 }
1243
1244 int symmetryType;
1245 float delta;
1246 Mat kernel;
1247};

1259 }

1262 {

1264 return 0;
1265

1270

1272 {

1274 __m128 f, s0 = _mm_setzero_ps(), s1 = s0, x0, x1;

1276 {

1278 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1279

1281 __m128i x1i = _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0i, x0i), 16);
1282 x0i = _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0i, x0i), 16);
1283 x0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(x0i);
1284 x1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(x1i);
1285 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1286 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1287 }
1288 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, s0);
1289 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1290 }
1291 return i;
1292 }

1294 Mat kernel;
1295 bool sse2_supported;
1296};

1299struct SymmColumnVec_32f16s
1300{
1301 SymmColumnVec_32f16s() { symmetryType=0; }
1302 SymmColumnVec_32f16s(const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType, int, double _delta)
1303 {
1304 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
1305 kernel = _kernel;
1306 delta = (float)_delta;
1307 CV_Assert( (symmetryType & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL | KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) != 0 );
1308 sse2_supported = checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2);
1309 }
1310
1311 int operator()(const uchar** _src, uchar* _dst, int width) const
1312 {
1313 if( !sse2_supported )
1314 return 0;
1315
1316 int ksize2 = (kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1)/2;
1317 const float* ky = (const float*)kernel.data + ksize2;
1318 int i = 0, k;
1319 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
1320 const float** src = (const float**)_src;
1321 const float *S, *S2;
1322 short* dst = (short*)_dst;
1323 __m128 d4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
1324
1325 if( symmetrical )
1326 {
1327 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
1328 {
1329 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
1330 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1331 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1332 __m128 x0, x1;
1333 S = src[0] + i;
1334 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S);
1335 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S+4);
1336 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1337 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s1, f), d4);
1338 s2 = _mm_load_ps(S+8);
1339 s3 = _mm_load_ps(S+12);
1340 s2 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s2, f), d4);
1341 s3 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s3, f), d4);
1342
1343 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1344 {
1345 S = src[k] + i;
1346 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1347 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1348 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1349 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S), _mm_load_ps(S2));
1350 x1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+4), _mm_load_ps(S2+4));
1351 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1352 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1353 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+8), _mm_load_ps(S2+8));
1354 x1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+12), _mm_load_ps(S2+12));
1355 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1356 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1357 }
1358
1359 __m128i s0i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1360 __m128i s1i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1);
1361 __m128i s2i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s2);
1362 __m128i s3i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s3);
1363
1364 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0i, s1i));
1365 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_packs_epi32(s2i, s3i));
1366 }
1367
1368 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1369 {
1370 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
1371 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1372 __m128 x0, s0 = _mm_load_ps(src[0] + i);
1373 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1374
1375 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1376 {
1377 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1378 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1379 S = src[k] + i;
1380 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1381 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(src[k]+i), _mm_load_ps(src[-k] + i));
1382 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1383 }
1384
1385 __m128i s0i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1386 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0i, s0i));
1387 }
1388 }
1389 else
1390 {
1391 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
1392 {
1393 __m128 f, s0 = d4, s1 = d4, s2 = d4, s3 = d4;
1394 __m128 x0, x1;
1395 S = src[0] + i;
1396
1397 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1398 {
1399 S = src[k] + i;
1400 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1401 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1402 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1403 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S), _mm_load_ps(S2));
1404 x1 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+4), _mm_load_ps(S2+4));
1405 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1406 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1407 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+8), _mm_load_ps(S2+8));
1408 x1 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+12), _mm_load_ps(S2+12));
1409 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1410 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1411 }
1412
1413 __m128i s0i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1414 __m128i s1i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1);
1415 __m128i s2i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s2);
1416 __m128i s3i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s3);
1417
1418 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0i, s1i));
1419 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i + 8), _mm_packs_epi32(s2i, s3i));
1420 }
1421
1422 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1423 {
1424 __m128 f, x0, s0 = d4;
1425
1426 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1427 {
1428 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1429 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1430 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(src[k]+i), _mm_load_ps(src[-k] + i));
1431 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1432 }
1433
1434 __m128i s0i = _mm_cvtps_epi32(s0);
1435 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst + i), _mm_packs_epi32(s0i, s0i));
1436 }
1437 }
1438
1439 return i;
1440 }
1441
1442 int symmetryType;
1443 float delta;
1444 Mat kernel;
1445 bool sse2_supported;
1446};

1450
1451struct RowVec_32f
1452{
1453 RowVec_32f() {}
1454 RowVec_32f( const Mat& _kernel )
1455 {
1456 kernel = _kernel;
1457 haveSSE = checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE);
1458#ifdef USE_IPP_SEP_FILTERS
1459 bufsz = -1;
1460#endif
1461 }
1462
1463 int operator()(const uchar* _src, uchar* _dst, int width, int cn) const
1464 {
1465 int _ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
1466 const float* src0 = (const float*)_src;
1467 float* dst = (float*)_dst;
1468 const float* _kx = (const float*)kernel.data;
1469
1470#ifdef USE_IPP_SEP_FILTERS
1471 IppiSize roisz = { width, 1 };
1472 if( (cn == 1 || cn == 3) && width >= _ksize*8 )
1473 {
1474 if( bufsz < 0 )
1475 {
1476 if( (cn == 1 && ippiFilterRowBorderPipelineGetBufferSize_32f_C1R(roisz, _ksize, &bufsz) < 0) ||
1477 (cn == 3 && ippiFilterRowBorderPipelineGetBufferSize_32f_C3R(roisz, _ksize, &bufsz) < 0))
1478 return 0;
1479 }
1480 AutoBuffer<uchar> buf(bufsz + 64);
1481 uchar* bufptr = alignPtr((uchar*)buf, 32);
1482 int step = (int)(width*sizeof(dst[0])*cn);
1483 float borderValue[] = {0.f, 0.f, 0.f};
1484 // here is the trick. IPP needs border type and extrapolates the row. We did it already.
1485 // So we pass anchor=0 and ignore the right tail of results since they are incorrect there.
1486 if( (cn == 1 && ippiFilterRowBorderPipeline_32f_C1R(src0, step, &dst, roisz, _kx, _ksize, 0,
1487 ippBorderRepl, borderValue[0], bufptr) < 0) ||
1488 (cn == 3 && ippiFilterRowBorderPipeline_32f_C3R(src0, step, &dst, roisz, _kx, _ksize, 0,
1489 ippBorderRepl, borderValue, bufptr) < 0))
1490 return 0;
1491 return width - _ksize + 1;
1492 }
1493#endif
1494
1495 if( !haveSSE )
1496 return 0;
1497
1498 int i = 0, k;
1499 width *= cn;
1500
1501 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1502 {
1503 const float* src = src0 + i;
1504 __m128 f, s0 = _mm_setzero_ps(), s1 = s0, x0, x1;
1505 for( k = 0; k < _ksize; k++, src += cn )
1506 {
1507 f = _mm_load_ss(_kx+k);
1508 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1509
1510 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1511 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1512 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1513 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1514 }
1515 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, s0);
1516 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1517 }
1518 return i;
1519 }
1520
1521 Mat kernel;
1522 bool haveSSE;
1523#ifdef USE_IPP_SEP_FILTERS
1524 mutable int bufsz;
1525#endif
1526};

1529struct SymmRowSmallVec_32f
1530{
1531 SymmRowSmallVec_32f() {}
1532 SymmRowSmallVec_32f( const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType )
1533 {
1534 kernel = _kernel;
1535 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
1536 }
1537
1538 int operator()(const uchar* _src, uchar* _dst, int width, int cn) const
1539 {
1540 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE) )
1541 return 0;
1542
1543 int i = 0, _ksize = kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1;
1544 float* dst = (float*)_dst;
1545 const float* src = (const float*)_src + (_ksize/2)*cn;
1546 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
1547 const float* kx = (const float*)kernel.data + _ksize/2;
1548 width *= cn;
1549
1550 if( symmetrical )
1551 {
1552 if( _ksize == 1 )
1553 return 0;
1554 if( _ksize == 3 )
1555 {
1556 if( kx[0] == 2 && kx[1] == 1 )
1557 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1558 {
1559 __m128 x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
1560 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1561 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1562 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1563 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1564 y1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1565 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1566 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_add_ps(_mm_add_ps(x1, x1), x2));
1567 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_add_ps(_mm_add_ps(y1, y1), y2));
1568 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1569 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1570 }
1571 else if( kx[0] == -2 && kx[1] == 1 )
1572 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1573 {
1574 __m128 x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
1575 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1576 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1577 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1578 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1579 y1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1580 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1581 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_sub_ps(x2, _mm_add_ps(x1, x1)));
1582 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_sub_ps(y2, _mm_add_ps(y1, y1)));
1583 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1584 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1585 }
1586 else
1587 {
1588 __m128 k0 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[0]), k1 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[1]);
1589 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1590 {
1591 __m128 x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
1592 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1593 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1594 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1595 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1596 y1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1597 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1598
1599 x0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_add_ps(x0, x2), k1);
1600 y0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_add_ps(y0, y2), k1);
1601 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_mul_ps(x1, k0));
1602 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_mul_ps(y1, k0));
1603 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1604 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1605 }
1606 }
1607 }
1608 else if( _ksize == 5 )
1609 {
1610 if( kx[0] == -2 && kx[1] == 0 && kx[2] == 1 )
1611 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1612 {
1613 __m128 x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
1614 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2);
1615 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1616 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2);
1617 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2 + 4);
1618 y1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1619 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2 + 4);
1620 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_sub_ps(x2, _mm_add_ps(x1, x1)));
1621 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_sub_ps(y2, _mm_add_ps(y1, y1)));
1622 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1623 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1624 }
1625 else
1626 {
1627 __m128 k0 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[0]), k1 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[1]), k2 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[2]);
1628 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1629 {
1630 __m128 x0, x1, x2, y0, y1, y2;
1631 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1632 x1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src);
1633 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1634 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1635 y1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + 4);
1636 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1637
1638 x0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_add_ps(x0, x2), k1);
1639 y0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_add_ps(y0, y2), k1);
1640 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_mul_ps(x1, k0));
1641 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_mul_ps(y1, k0));
1642
1643 x2 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2), _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2));
1644 y2 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2 + 4), _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2 + 4));
1645 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_mul_ps(x2, k2));
1646 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_mul_ps(y2, k2));
1647
1648 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1649 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1650 }
1651 }
1652 }
1653 }
1654 else
1655 {
1656 if( _ksize == 3 )
1657 {
1658 if( kx[0] == 0 && kx[1] == 1 )
1659 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1660 {
1661 __m128 x0, x2, y0, y2;
1662 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1663 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1664 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1665 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1666 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(x0, x2);
1667 y0 = _mm_sub_ps(y0, y2);
1668 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1669 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1670 }
1671 else
1672 {
1673 __m128 k1 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[1]);
1674 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1675 {
1676 __m128 x0, x2, y0, y2;
1677 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1678 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1679 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1680 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1681
1682 x0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_sub_ps(x0, x2), k1);
1683 y0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_sub_ps(y0, y2), k1);
1684 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1685 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1686 }
1687 }
1688 }
1689 else if( _ksize == 5 )
1690 {
1691 __m128 k1 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[1]), k2 = _mm_set1_ps(kx[2]);
1692 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8, src += 8 )
1693 {
1694 __m128 x0, x2, y0, y2;
1695 x0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn);
1696 x2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn);
1697 y0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src + cn + 4);
1698 y2 = _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn + 4);
1699
1700 x0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_sub_ps(x0, x2), k1);
1701 y0 = _mm_mul_ps(_mm_sub_ps(y0, y2), k1);
1702
1703 x2 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2), _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2));
1704 y2 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_loadu_ps(src + cn*2 + 4), _mm_loadu_ps(src - cn*2 + 4));
1705 x0 = _mm_add_ps(x0, _mm_mul_ps(x2, k2));
1706 y0 = _mm_add_ps(y0, _mm_mul_ps(y2, k2));
1707
1708 _mm_store_ps(dst + i, x0);
1709 _mm_store_ps(dst + i + 4, y0);
1710 }
1711 }
1712 }
1713
1714 return i;
1715 }
1716
1717 Mat kernel;
1718 int symmetryType;
1719};

1722struct SymmColumnVec_32f
1723{
1724 SymmColumnVec_32f() { symmetryType=0; }
1725 SymmColumnVec_32f(const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType, int, double _delta)
1726 {
1727 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
1728 kernel = _kernel;
1729 delta = (float)_delta;
1730 CV_Assert( (symmetryType & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL | KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) != 0 );
1731 }
1732
1733 int operator()(const uchar** _src, uchar* _dst, int width) const
1734 {
1735 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE) )
1736 return 0;
1737
1738 int ksize2 = (kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1)/2;
1739 const float* ky = (const float*)kernel.data + ksize2;
1740 int i = 0, k;
1741 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
1742 const float** src = (const float**)_src;
1743 const float *S, *S2;
1744 float* dst = (float*)_dst;
1745 __m128 d4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
1746
1747 if( symmetrical )
1748 {
1749 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
1750 {
1751 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
1752 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1753 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1754 __m128 x0, x1;
1755 S = src[0] + i;
1756 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S);
1757 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S+4);
1758 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1759 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s1, f), d4);
1760 s2 = _mm_load_ps(S+8);
1761 s3 = _mm_load_ps(S+12);
1762 s2 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s2, f), d4);
1763 s3 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s3, f), d4);
1764
1765 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1766 {
1767 S = src[k] + i;
1768 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1769 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1770 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1771 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S), _mm_load_ps(S2));
1772 x1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+4), _mm_load_ps(S2+4));
1773 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1774 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1775 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+8), _mm_load_ps(S2+8));
1776 x1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+12), _mm_load_ps(S2+12));
1777 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1778 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1779 }
1780
1781 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1782 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1783 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 8, s2);
1784 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 12, s3);
1785 }
1786
1787 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1788 {
1789 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(ky);
1790 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1791 __m128 x0, s0 = _mm_load_ps(src[0] + i);
1792 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, f), d4);
1793
1794 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1795 {
1796 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1797 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1798 S = src[k] + i;
1799 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1800 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(src[k]+i), _mm_load_ps(src[-k] + i));
1801 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1802 }
1803
1804 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1805 }
1806 }
1807 else
1808 {
1809 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
1810 {
1811 __m128 f, s0 = d4, s1 = d4, s2 = d4, s3 = d4;
1812 __m128 x0, x1;
1813 S = src[0] + i;
1814
1815 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1816 {
1817 S = src[k] + i;
1818 S2 = src[-k] + i;
1819 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1820 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1821 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S), _mm_load_ps(S2));
1822 x1 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+4), _mm_load_ps(S2+4));
1823 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1824 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1825 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+8), _mm_load_ps(S2+8));
1826 x1 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S+12), _mm_load_ps(S2+12));
1827 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1828 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(x1, f));
1829 }
1830
1831 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1832 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1833 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 8, s2);
1834 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 12, s3);
1835 }
1836
1837 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
1838 {
1839 __m128 f, x0, s0 = d4;
1840
1841 for( k = 1; k <= ksize2; k++ )
1842 {
1843 f = _mm_load_ss(ky+k);
1844 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
1845 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(src[k]+i), _mm_load_ps(src[-k] + i));
1846 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0, f));
1847 }
1848
1849 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1850 }
1851 }
1852
1853 return i;
1854 }
1855
1856 int symmetryType;
1857 float delta;
1858 Mat kernel;
1859};

1862struct SymmColumnSmallVec_32f
1863{
1864 SymmColumnSmallVec_32f() { symmetryType=0; }
1865 SymmColumnSmallVec_32f(const Mat& _kernel, int _symmetryType, int, double _delta)
1866 {
1867 symmetryType = _symmetryType;
1868 kernel = _kernel;
1869 delta = (float)_delta;
1870 CV_Assert( (symmetryType & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL | KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) != 0 );
1871 }
1872
1873 int operator()(const uchar** _src, uchar* _dst, int width) const
1874 {
1875 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE) )
1876 return 0;
1877
1878 int ksize2 = (kernel.rows + kernel.cols - 1)/2;
1879 const float* ky = (const float*)kernel.data + ksize2;
1880 int i = 0;
1881 bool symmetrical = (symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
1882 const float** src = (const float**)_src;
1883 const float *S0 = src[-1], *S1 = src[0], *S2 = src[1];
1884 float* dst = (float*)_dst;
1885 __m128 d4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
1886
1887 if( symmetrical )
1888 {
1889 if( ky[0] == 2 && ky[1] == 1 )
1890 {
1891 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1892 {
1893 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3, s4, s5;
1894 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i);
1895 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i + 4);
1896 s2 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i);
1897 s3 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i + 4);
1898 s4 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i);
1899 s5 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i + 4);
1900 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_add_ps(s4, _mm_add_ps(s2, s2)));
1901 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_add_ps(s5, _mm_add_ps(s3, s3)));
1902 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, d4);
1903 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, d4);
1904 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1905 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1906 }
1907 }
1908 else if( ky[0] == -2 && ky[1] == 1 )
1909 {
1910 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1911 {
1912 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3, s4, s5;
1913 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i);
1914 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i + 4);
1915 s2 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i);
1916 s3 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i + 4);
1917 s4 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i);
1918 s5 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i + 4);
1919 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_sub_ps(s4, _mm_add_ps(s2, s2)));
1920 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_sub_ps(s5, _mm_add_ps(s3, s3)));
1921 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, d4);
1922 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, d4);
1923 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1924 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1925 }
1926 }
1927 else
1928 {
1929 __m128 k0 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[0]), k1 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[1]);
1930 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1931 {
1932 __m128 s0, s1, x0, x1;
1933 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i);
1934 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S1 + i + 4);
1935 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s0, k0), d4);
1936 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(s1, k0), d4);
1937 x0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S0 + i), _mm_load_ps(S2 + i));
1938 x1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_load_ps(S0 + i + 4), _mm_load_ps(S2 + i + 4));
1939 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0,k1));
1940 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1,k1));
1941 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1942 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1943 }
1944 }
1945 }
1946 else
1947 {
1948 if( fabs(ky[1]) == 1 && ky[1] == -ky[-1] )
1949 {
1950 if( ky[1] < 0 )
1951 std::swap(S0, S2);
1952 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1953 {
1954 __m128 s0, s1, s2, s3;
1955 s0 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i);
1956 s1 = _mm_load_ps(S2 + i + 4);
1957 s2 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i);
1958 s3 = _mm_load_ps(S0 + i + 4);
1959 s0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_sub_ps(s0, s2), d4);
1960 s1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_sub_ps(s1, s3), d4);
1961 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1962 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1963 }
1964 }
1965 else
1966 {
1967 __m128 k1 = _mm_set1_ps(ky[1]);
1968 for( ; i <= width - 8; i += 8 )
1969 {
1970 __m128 s0 = d4, s1 = d4, x0, x1;
1971 x0 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S2 + i), _mm_load_ps(S0 + i));
1972 x1 = _mm_sub_ps(_mm_load_ps(S2 + i + 4), _mm_load_ps(S0 + i + 4));
1973 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(x0,k1));
1974 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(x1,k1));
1975 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i, s0);
1976 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + i + 4, s1);
1977 }
1978 }
1979 }
1980
1981 return i;
1982 }
1983
1984 int symmetryType;
1985 float delta;
1986 Mat kernel;
1987};

1992///////////////////////////////// 8u<->8u, 8u<->16s /////////////////////////////////
1993
1994struct FilterVec_8u
1995{
1996 FilterVec_8u() {}
1997 FilterVec_8u(const Mat& _kernel, int _bits, double _delta)
1998 {
1999 Mat kernel;
2000 _kernel.convertTo(kernel, CV_32F, 1./(1 << _bits), 0);
2001 delta = (float)(_delta/(1 << _bits));
2002 vector<Point> coords;
2003 preprocess2DKernel(kernel, coords, coeffs);
2004 _nz = (int)coords.size();
2005 }
2006
2007 int operator()(const uchar** src, uchar* dst, int width) const
2008 {
2009 if( !checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2) )
2010 return 0;
2011
2012 const float* kf = (const float*)&coeffs[0];
2013 int i = 0, k, nz = _nz;
2014 __m128 d4 = _mm_set1_ps(delta);
2015
2016 for( ; i <= width - 16; i += 16 )
2017 {
2018 __m128 s0 = d4, s1 = d4, s2 = d4, s3 = d4;
2019 __m128i x0, x1, z = _mm_setzero_si128();
2020
2021 for( k = 0; k < nz; k++ )
2022 {
2023 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(kf+k), t0, t1;
2024 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
2025
2026 x0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src[k] + i));
2027 x1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(x0, z);
2028 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
2029
2030 t0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, z));
2031 t1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x0, z));
2032 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(t0, f));
2033 s1 = _mm_add_ps(s1, _mm_mul_ps(t1, f));
2034
2035 t0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x1, z));
2036 t1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(x1, z));
2037 s2 = _mm_add_ps(s2, _mm_mul_ps(t0, f));
2038 s3 = _mm_add_ps(s3, _mm_mul_ps(t1, f));
2039 }
2040
2041 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s1));
2042 x1 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s2), _mm_cvtps_epi32(s3));
2043 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x1);
2044 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + i), x0);
2045 }
2046
2047 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2048 {
2049 __m128 s0 = d4;
2050 __m128i x0, z = _mm_setzero_si128();
2051
2052 for( k = 0; k < nz; k++ )
2053 {
2054 __m128 f = _mm_load_ss(kf+k), t0;
2055 f = _mm_shuffle_ps(f, f, 0);
2056
2057 x0 = _mm_cvtsi32_si128(*(const int*)(src[k] + i));
2058 x0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(x0, z);
2059 t0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(x0, z));
2060 s0 = _mm_add_ps(s0, _mm_mul_ps(t0, f));
2061 }
2062
2063 x0 = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(s0), z);
2064 x0 = _mm_packus_epi16(x0, x0);
2065 *(int*)(dst + i) = _mm_cvtsi128_si32(x0);
2066 }
2067
2068 return i;
2069 }

2626 const VecOp& _vecOp=VecOp())
2627 : SymmColumnFilter<CastOp, VecOp>( _kernel, _anchor, _delta, _symmetryType, _castOp, _vecOp )
2628 {
2629 CV_Assert( this->ksize == 3 );
2630 }
2631
2632 void operator()(const uchar** src, uchar* dst, int dststep, int count, int width)
2633 {
2634 int ksize2 = this->ksize/2;
2635 const ST* ky = (const ST*)this->kernel.data + ksize2;
2636 int i;
2637 bool symmetrical = (this->symmetryType & KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL) != 0;
2638 bool is_1_2_1 = ky[0] == 2 && ky[1] == 1;
2639 bool is_1_m2_1 = ky[0] == -2 && ky[1] == 1;
2640 bool is_m1_0_1 = (ky[1] == 1 || ky[1] == -1) && ky[1] == -ky[-1] && ky[0] == 0;
2641 ST f0 = ky[0], f1 = ky[1];
2642 ST _delta = this->delta;
2643 CastOp castOp = this->castOp0;
2644 src += ksize2;
2645
2646 for( ; count--; dst += dststep, src++ )
2647 {
2648 DT* D = (DT*)dst;
2649 i = (this->vecOp)(src, dst, width);
2650 const ST* S0 = (const ST*)src[-1];
2651 const ST* S1 = (const ST*)src[0];
2652 const ST* S2 = (const ST*)src[1];
2653
2654 if( symmetrical )
2655 {
2656 if( is_1_2_1 )
2657 {
2658 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2659 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2660 {
2661 ST s0 = S0[i] + S1[i]*2 + S2[i] + _delta;
2662 ST s1 = S0[i+1] + S1[i+1]*2 + S2[i+1] + _delta;
2663 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2664 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2665
2666 s0 = S0[i+2] + S1[i+2]*2 + S2[i+2] + _delta;
2667 s1 = S0[i+3] + S1[i+3]*2 + S2[i+3] + _delta;
2668 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2669 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2670 }
2671 #endif
2672 for( ; i < width; i ++ )
2673 {
2674 ST s0 = S0[i] + S1[i]*2 + S2[i] + _delta;
2675 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2676 }
2677 }
2678 else if( is_1_m2_1 )
2679 {
2680 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2681 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2682 {
2683 ST s0 = S0[i] - S1[i]*2 + S2[i] + _delta;
2684 ST s1 = S0[i+1] - S1[i+1]*2 + S2[i+1] + _delta;
2685 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2686 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2687
2688 s0 = S0[i+2] - S1[i+2]*2 + S2[i+2] + _delta;
2689 s1 = S0[i+3] - S1[i+3]*2 + S2[i+3] + _delta;
2690 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2691 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2692 }
2693 #endif
2694 for( ; i < width; i ++ )
2695 {
2696 ST s0 = S0[i] - S1[i]*2 + S2[i] + _delta;
2697 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2698 }
2699 }
2700 else
2701 {
2702 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2703 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2704 {
2705 ST s0 = (S0[i] + S2[i])*f1 + S1[i]*f0 + _delta;
2706 ST s1 = (S0[i+1] + S2[i+1])*f1 + S1[i+1]*f0 + _delta;
2707 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2708 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2709
2710 s0 = (S0[i+2] + S2[i+2])*f1 + S1[i+2]*f0 + _delta;
2711 s1 = (S0[i+3] + S2[i+3])*f1 + S1[i+3]*f0 + _delta;
2712 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2713 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2714 }
2715 #endif
2716 for( ; i < width; i ++ )
2717 {
2718 ST s0 = (S0[i] + S2[i])*f1 + S1[i]*f0 + _delta;
2719 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2720 }
2721 }
2722 for( ; i < width; i++ )
2723 D[i] = castOp((S0[i] + S2[i])*f1 + S1[i]*f0 + _delta);
2724 }
2725 else
2726 {
2727 if( is_m1_0_1 )
2728 {
2729 if( f1 < 0 )
2730 std::swap(S0, S2);
2731 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2732 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2733 {
2734 ST s0 = S2[i] - S0[i] + _delta;
2735 ST s1 = S2[i+1] - S0[i+1] + _delta;
2736 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2737 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2738
2739 s0 = S2[i+2] - S0[i+2] + _delta;
2740 s1 = S2[i+3] - S0[i+3] + _delta;
2741 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2742 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2743 }
2744 #endif
2745 for( ; i < width; i ++ )
2746 {
2747 ST s0 = S2[i] - S0[i] + _delta;
2748 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2749 }
2750 }
2751 else if( ky[0] == 0 )
2752 {
2753 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2754 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2755 {
2756 ST s0 = (S2[i] - S0[i])*f1 + _delta;
2757 ST s1 = (S2[i+1] - S0[i+1])*f1 + _delta;
2758 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2759 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2760
2761 s0 = (S2[i+2] - S0[i+2])*f1 + _delta;
2762 s1 = (S2[i+3] - S0[i+3])*f1 + _delta;
2763 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2764 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2765 }
2766 #endif
2767 for( ; i < width; i++ )
2768 D[i] = castOp((S2[i] - S0[i])*f1 + _delta);
2769 }
2770 else
2771 {
2772 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2773 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
2774 {
2775 ST s0 = (S2[i] - S0[i])*f1 + S1[i]*f0 + _delta;
2776 ST s1 = (S2[i+1] - S0[i+1])*f1 + S1[i+1]*f0 + _delta;
2777 D[i] = castOp(s0);
2778 D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
2779
2780 s0 = (S2[i+2] - S0[i+2])*f1 + S1[i+2]*f0 + _delta;
2781 s1 = (S2[i+3] - S0[i+3])*f1 + S1[i+2]*f0 + _delta;
2782 D[i+2] = castOp(s0);
2783 D[i+3] = castOp(s1);
2784 }
2785 #endif
2786 for( ; i < width; i++ )
2787 D[i] = castOp((S2[i] - S0[i])*f1 + S1[i]*f0 + _delta);
2788 }
2789
2790 }
2791 }
2792 }
2793};
2794
2795template<typename ST, typename DT> struct Cast
2796{
2797 typedef ST type1;
2798 typedef DT rtype;
2799
2800 DT operator()(ST val) const { return saturate_cast<DT>(val); }
2801};
2802
2803template<typename ST, typename DT, int bits> struct FixedPtCast
2804{
2805 typedef ST type1;
2806 typedef DT rtype;
2807 enum { SHIFT = bits, DELTA = 1 << (bits-1) };
2808
2809 DT operator()(ST val) const { return saturate_cast<DT>((val + DELTA)>>SHIFT); }
2810};
2811
2812template<typename ST, typename DT> struct FixedPtCastEx
2813{
2814 typedef ST type1;
2815 typedef DT rtype;
2816
2817 FixedPtCastEx() : SHIFT(0), DELTA(0) {}
2818 FixedPtCastEx(int bits) : SHIFT(bits), DELTA(bits ? 1 << (bits-1) : 0) {}
2819 DT operator()(ST val) const { return saturate_cast<DT>((val + DELTA)>>SHIFT); }
2820 int SHIFT, DELTA;
2821};
2822
2823}

2976cv::Ptr<cv::FilterEngine> cv::createSeparableLinearFilter(
2977 int _srcType, int _dstType,
2978 InputArray __rowKernel, InputArray __columnKernel,
2979 Point _anchor, double _delta,
2980 int _rowBorderType, int _columnBorderType,
2981 const Scalar& _borderValue )
2982{
2983 Mat _rowKernel = __rowKernel.getMat(), _columnKernel = __columnKernel.getMat();
2984 _srcType = CV_MAT_TYPE(_srcType);
2985 _dstType = CV_MAT_TYPE(_dstType);
2986 int sdepth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(_srcType), ddepth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(_dstType);
2987 int cn = CV_MAT_CN(_srcType);
2988 CV_Assert( cn == CV_MAT_CN(_dstType) );
2989 int rsize = _rowKernel.rows + _rowKernel.cols - 1;
2990 int csize = _columnKernel.rows + _columnKernel.cols - 1;
2991 if( _anchor.x < 0 )
2992 _anchor.x = rsize/2;
2993 if( _anchor.y < 0 )
2994 _anchor.y = csize/2;
2995 int rtype = getKernelType(_rowKernel,
2996 _rowKernel.rows == 1 ? Point(_anchor.x, 0) : Point(0, _anchor.x));
2997 int ctype = getKernelType(_columnKernel,
2998 _columnKernel.rows == 1 ? Point(_anchor.y, 0) : Point(0, _anchor.y));
2999 Mat rowKernel, columnKernel;
3000
3001 int bdepth = std::max(CV_32F,std::max(sdepth, ddepth));
3002 int bits = 0;
3003
3004 if( sdepth == CV_8U &&
3005 ((rtype == KERNEL_SMOOTH+KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL &&
3006 ctype == KERNEL_SMOOTH+KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL &&
3007 ddepth == CV_8U) ||
3008 ((rtype & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL+KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) &&
3009 (ctype & (KERNEL_SYMMETRICAL+KERNEL_ASYMMETRICAL)) &&
3010 (rtype & ctype & KERNEL_INTEGER) &&
3011 ddepth == CV_16S)) )
3012 {
3013 bdepth = CV_32S;
3014 bits = ddepth == CV_8U ? 8 : 0;
3015 _rowKernel.convertTo( rowKernel, CV_32S, 1 << bits );
3016 _columnKernel.convertTo( columnKernel, CV_32S, 1 << bits );
3017 bits *= 2;
3018 _delta *= (1 << bits);
3019 }
3020 else
3021 {
3022 if( _rowKernel.type() != bdepth )
3023 _rowKernel.convertTo( rowKernel, bdepth );
3024 else
3025 rowKernel = _rowKernel;
3026 if( _columnKernel.type() != bdepth )
3027 _columnKernel.convertTo( columnKernel, bdepth );
3028 else
3029 columnKernel = _columnKernel;
3030 }
3031
3032 int _bufType = CV_MAKETYPE(bdepth, cn);
3033 Ptr<BaseRowFilter> _rowFilter = getLinearRowFilter(
3034 _srcType, _bufType, rowKernel, _anchor.x, rtype);
3035 Ptr<BaseColumnFilter> _columnFilter = getLinearColumnFilter(
3036 _bufType, _dstType, columnKernel, _anchor.y, ctype, _delta, bits );
3037
3038 return Ptr<FilterEngine>( new FilterEngine(Ptr<BaseFilter>(0), _rowFilter, _columnFilter,
3039 _srcType, _dstType, _bufType, _rowBorderType, _columnBorderType, _borderValue ));
3040}

3049
3050void preprocess2DKernel( const Mat& kernel, vector<Point>& coords, vector<uchar>& coeffs )
3051{
3052 int i, j, k, nz = countNonZero(kernel), ktype = kernel.type();
3053 if(nz == 0)
3054 nz = 1;
3055 CV_Assert( ktype == CV_8U || ktype == CV_32S || ktype == CV_32F || ktype == CV_64F );
3056 coords.resize(nz);
3057 coeffs.resize(nz*getElemSize(ktype));
3058 uchar* _coeffs = &coeffs[0];
3059
3060 for( i = k = 0; i < kernel.rows; i++ )
3061 {
3062 const uchar* krow = kernel.data + kernel.step*i;
3063 for( j = 0; j < kernel.cols; j++ )
3064 {
3065 if( ktype == CV_8U )
3066 {
3067 uchar val = krow[j];
3068 if( val == 0 )
3069 continue;
3070 coords[k] = Point(j,i);
3071 _coeffs[k++] = val;
3072 }
3073 else if( ktype == CV_32S )
3074 {
3075 int val = ((const int*)krow)[j];
3076 if( val == 0 )
3077 continue;
3078 coords[k] = Point(j,i);
3079 ((int*)_coeffs)[k++] = val;
3080 }
3081 else if( ktype == CV_32F )
3082 {
3083 float val = ((const float*)krow)[j];
3084 if( val == 0 )
3085 continue;
3086 coords[k] = Point(j,i);
3087 ((float*)_coeffs)[k++] = val;
3088 }
3089 else
3090 {
3091 double val = ((const double*)krow)[j];
3092 if( val == 0 )
3093 continue;
3094 coords[k] = Point(j,i);
3095 ((double*)_coeffs)[k++] = val;
3096 }
3097 }
3098 }
3099}

3102template<typename ST, class CastOp, class VecOp> struct Filter2D : public BaseFilter
3103{
3104 typedef typename CastOp::type1 KT;
3105 typedef typename CastOp::rtype DT;
3106
3107 Filter2D( const Mat& _kernel, Point _anchor,
3108 double _delta, const CastOp& _castOp=CastOp(),
3109 const VecOp& _vecOp=VecOp() )
3110 {
3111 anchor = _anchor;
3112 ksize = _kernel.size();
3113 delta = saturate_cast<KT>(_delta);
3114 castOp0 = _castOp;
3115 vecOp = _vecOp;
3116 CV_Assert( _kernel.type() == DataType<KT>::type );
3117 preprocess2DKernel( _kernel, coords, coeffs );
3118 ptrs.resize( coords.size() );
3119 }
3120
3121 void operator()(const uchar** src, uchar* dst, int dststep, int count, int width, int cn)
3122 {
3123 KT _delta = delta;
3124 const Point* pt = &coords[0];
3125 const KT* kf = (const KT*)&coeffs[0];
3126 const ST** kp = (const ST**)&ptrs[0];
3127 int i, k, nz = (int)coords.size();
3128 CastOp castOp = castOp0;
3129
3130 width *= cn;
3131 for( ; count > 0; count--, dst += dststep, src++ )
3132 {
3133 DT* D = (DT*)dst;
3134
3135 for( k = 0; k < nz; k++ )
3136 kp[k] = (const ST*)src[pt[k].y] + pt[k].x*cn;
3137
3138 i = vecOp((const uchar**)kp, dst, width);
3139 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
3140 for( ; i <= width - 4; i += 4 )
3141 {
3142 KT s0 = _delta, s1 = _delta, s2 = _delta, s3 = _delta;
3143
3144 for( k = 0; k < nz; k++ )
3145 {
3146 const ST* sptr = kp[k] + i;
3147 KT f = kf[k];
3148 s0 += f*sptr[0];
3149 s1 += f*sptr[1];
3150 s2 += f*sptr[2];
3151 s3 += f*sptr[3];
3152 }
3153
3154 D[i] = castOp(s0); D[i+1] = castOp(s1);
3155 D[i+2] = castOp(s2); D[i+3] = castOp(s3);
3156 }
3157 #endif
3158 for( ; i < width; i++ )
3159 {
3160 KT s0 = _delta;
3161 for( k = 0; k < nz; k++ )
3162 s0 += kf[k]*kp[k][i];
3163 D[i] = castOp(s0);
3164 }
3165 }
3166 }
3167
3168 vector<Point> coords;
3169 vector<uchar> coeffs;
3170 vector<uchar*> ptrs;
3171 KT delta;
3172 CastOp castOp0;
3173 VecOp vecOp;
3174};

3197
3198 kdepth = sdepth == CV_64F || ddepth == CV_64F ? CV_64F : CV_32F;
3199 Mat kernel;
3200 if( _kernel.type() == kdepth )
3201 kernel = _kernel;
3202 else
3203 _kernel.convertTo(kernel, kdepth, _kernel.type() == CV_32S ? 1./(1 << bits) : 1.);

3219 Cast<double, double>, FilterNoVec>(kernel, anchor, delta));
3220
3221 if( sdepth == CV_16U && ddepth == CV_16U )
3222 return Ptr<BaseFilter>(new Filter2D<ushort,
3223 Cast<float, ushort>, FilterNoVec>(kernel, anchor, delta));
3224 if( sdepth == CV_16U && ddepth == CV_32F )
3225 return Ptr<BaseFilter>(new Filter2D<ushort,

3227 if( sdepth == CV_16U && ddepth == CV_64F )

3237 if( sdepth == CV_16S && ddepth == CV_64F )

3250 srcType, dstType));

3289void cv::filter2D( InputArray _src, OutputArray _dst, int ddepth,
3290 InputArray _kernel, Point anchor,
3291 double delta, int borderType )
3292{
3293 Mat src = _src.getMat(), kernel = _kernel.getMat();
3294
3295 if( ddepth < 0 )
3296 ddepth = src.depth();
3297
3298#if CV_SSE2
3299 int dft_filter_size = ((src.depth() == CV_8U && (ddepth == CV_8U || ddepth == CV_16S)) ||
3300 (src.depth() == CV_32F && ddepth == CV_32F)) && checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE3)? 130 : 50;
3301#else
3302 int dft_filter_size = 50;
3303#endif
3304
3305 _dst.create( src.size(), CV_MAKETYPE(ddepth, src.channels()) );
3306 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
3307 anchor = normalizeAnchor(anchor, kernel.size());
3308
3309#ifdef HAVE_TEGRA_OPTIMIZATION
3310 if( tegra::filter2D(src, dst, kernel, anchor, delta, borderType) )
3311 return;
3312#endif
3313
3314 if( kernel.cols*kernel.rows >= dft_filter_size )
3315 {
3316 Mat temp;
3317 if( src.data != dst.data )
3318 temp = dst;
3319 else
3320 temp.create(dst.size(), dst.type());
3321 crossCorr( src, kernel, temp, src.size(),
3322 CV_MAKETYPE(ddepth, src.channels()),
3323 anchor, delta, borderType );
3324 if( temp.data != dst.data )
3325 temp.copyTo(dst);
3326 return;
3327 }
3328
3329 Ptr<FilterEngine> f = createLinearFilter(src.type(), dst.type(), kernel,
3330 anchor, delta, borderType & ~BORDER_ISOLATED );
3331 f->apply(src, dst, Rect(0,0,-1,-1), Point(), (borderType & BORDER_ISOLATED) != 0 );
3332}
